# ORIG TITLE    Cardinal Glemp dies aged 83 . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Cardinal Jozef Glemp, who played a central role in Poland’s peaceful transition from Communism to democracy has died aged 83. During Glemp’s 28-year tenure; until 2009; as primate of the country’s Roman Catholic Church; the Church guided the opposition to authoritarian rule and provided backing to Solidarity, the Communist bloc’s first independent trade union. 
